            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " production because of semiconductor shortages in the auto industry. After all, the sports car has been wildly popular and is not only helping Chevrolet’s image, it’s a big money maker. It, along with other vehicles with thick profit margins, like trucks, SUVs and high-end luxury cars, have been prioritized over models which aren’t such cash cows.",
